<p>Seeing the Houris in a dream indicates the gifts of God, the fulfillment of desires, and other interpretations. Seeing the Houris in Paradise, or kissing the Houris, or having intercourse with a <a href="https://gptafser.com/post/تفسير-حلم-حورية-البحر-في-المنام-لابن-سيرين?page=35" >mermaid</a>, or marrying mermaids, according to <a href="https://gptafser.com/post/تفسير-حلم-ابن-سيرين-في-المنام?page=1665" >Ibn Sirin</a> and others on the subject:</p>
<p><span></span></p>
<h2><span>Interpretation of the Houris in a Dream</span></h2>
<p>The Houris are a gift that God Almighty has given to the believers in Paradise for their good deeds in this world and for their adherence to the religion of God and the teachings of Islam. It is a place in the Hereafter.</p>
<p>Seeing <strong>poplar trees in a dream</strong> means that the dreamer will live a happy life, and the vision indicates that the dreamer will obtain sustenance.<br/>Also, seeing the Houris in a dream indicates that the dreamer will have a good end after his death and that God will reward him with good.</p><div class="angwp_84394 _ning_cont _ning_hidden _ning_outer _align_center responsive" data-aid="0" data-bid="84394" data-size="custom" style="max-width:100%; width:100%;height:inherit;"><div class="_ning_label _left" style=""></div><div class="_ning_inner" style=""><script type="text/javascript">
